Now we simplify the fraction to find the final probability.

The denominator becomes $1 - \frac{5}{6} = \frac{1}{6}$.

$$
\begin{aligned}
P(X \ge 4) &= \frac{\frac{125}{1296}}{\frac{1}{6}} \\
&= \frac{125}{1296} \times \frac{6}{1} \\
&= \frac{125}{216} 
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the probability is $\frac{125}{216}$.
